# {{companyName}} Superpowers

Enterprise AI coding superpowers for **{{companyName}}**, generated by [Enterprise Superpowers](https://github.com/idiaz01/enterprise-superpowers).

## Getting Started

### 1. Install the Plugin (Persistent)

Run the setup script to register the plugin in your Claude Code settings. It will load automatically in every session:

```bash
cd {{companySlug}}-superpowers
bash setup.sh
```

To load for a single session only (without persistent installation):

```bash
claude --plugin-dir ./{{companySlug}}-superpowers
```

Use `/reload-plugins` inside a session to pick up changes without restarting.

#### Team Distribution

For team-wide distribution, push the generated plugin to a GitHub repository and register it as a marketplace:

```bash
# Inside Claude Code:
/plugin marketplace add your-org/{{companySlug}}-superpowers
/plugin install {{companySlug}}-superpowers@your-org-marketplace
```

Or add it to your project's `.claude/settings.json` so all team members get it automatically:

```json
{
  "extraKnownMarketplaces": {
    "{{companySlug}}-superpowers": {
      "source": {
        "source": "github",
        "repo": "your-org/{{companySlug}}-superpowers"
      }
    }
  },
  "enabledPlugins": {
    "{{companySlug}}-superpowers@{{companySlug}}-superpowers": true
  }
}
```

#### Uninstall

```bash
bash uninstall.sh
```

### 2. Verify It's Working

In a Claude Code session, try any of the included slash commands:

```
/tdd
/code-review
/plan
```

You should see the skill activate with {{companyName}}-specific context. You can also ask Claude to "list available skills" to confirm the plugin loaded.

### 3. Configure MCP Servers

The generated `.mcp.json` includes pre-configured MCP servers with placeholder credentials. Open it and replace the `YOUR_*_HERE` values with your actual tokens.

**Required credentials by server:**

| Server | Env Variable | How to Get It |
|--------|-------------|---------------|
| **GitHub** | `GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN` | [github.com/settings/tokens](https://github.com/settings/tokens) — create a Fine-grained PAT |
| **Confluence** | `CONFLUENCE_BASE_URL`, `CONFLUENCE_EMAIL`, `CONFLUENCE_API_TOKEN` | [id.atlassian.com/manage-profile/security/api-tokens](https://id.atlassian.com/manage-profile/security/api-tokens) |
| **Notion** | `OPENAPI_MCP_HEADERS` (Bearer token) | [notion.so/profile/integrations](https://www.notion.so/profile/integrations) — create an internal integration |
| **Slack** | `SLACK_BOT_TOKEN`, `SLACK_TEAM_ID` | [api.slack.com/apps](https://api.slack.com/apps) — create an app and install to workspace |
| **AWS** | `AWS_PROFILE` | Configure via `aws configure` — uses your local AWS credentials |
| **Terraform** | `TFE_TOKEN` | [app.terraform.io/app/settings/tokens](https://app.terraform.io/app/settings/tokens) |
| **Grafana** | `GRAFANA_URL`, `GRAFANA_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_TOKEN` | Grafana → Administration → Service Accounts |
| **Linear** | `LINEAR_API_KEY` | [linear.app/settings/api](https://linear.app/settings/api) |
| **Firecrawl** | `FIRECRAWL_API_KEY` | [firecrawl.dev](https://www.firecrawl.dev/) |
| **Exa** | `EXA_API_KEY` | [dashboard.exa.ai](https://dashboard.exa.ai/) |
| **fal.ai** | `FAL_KEY` | [fal.ai/dashboard/keys](https://fal.ai/dashboard/keys) |
| **Browserbase** | `BROWSERBASE_API_KEY` | [browserbase.com](https://www.browserbase.com/) |
| **Supabase** | `--project-ref` in args | [supabase.com/dashboard](https://supabase.com/dashboard) — copy your project ref |
| **Filesystem** | Path in args | Replace `/path/to/your/projects` with your actual workspace path |

**Remove servers you don't use.** Keeping unused MCP servers configured won't break anything, but each one consumes context window when connected. Aim for fewer than 10 active servers.

### 4. Configure Hooks (Optional)

The `hooks/hooks.json` file includes quality gates, auto-formatting, and reminders. These run automatically during Claude Code sessions. Review and disable any you don't want:

- **PreToolUse** — Git push reminder, context compaction suggestions
- **PostToolUse** — Auto-format, TypeScript checking, console.log warnings, quality gates
- **Stop** — Console.log check on modified files
- **SessionStart** — Welcome message

To disable a hook, remove its entry from `hooks/hooks.json`.

## What's Included

### Design System

Your company's visual identity is baked into the `company-design-system` skill. When Claude creates presentations, HTML prototypes, or documentation, it uses your:

- **Brand colors** — defined in `config/design-system.json` and enforced via `rules/design-system.md`
- **Typography** — corporate fonts applied consistently across all generated content
- **Logos** — primary logo and icon/favicon stored in `assets/logos/` and referenced in headers, slides, and footers
